2. **Commercial use** — requires a separate paid commercial license. See the
   "Commercial Addendum" section after the PolyForm text.

---

## What's commercial vs. noncommercial (plain English summary)

NOT NORMATIVE — the legal definitions in the PolyForm text below govern. This
summary is to help you self-assess.

**Allowed for free** (noncommercial):
- Personal use on your own machine.
- Internal use inside your own company, by your own employees, for your own
  internal operations — even if your company is for-profit.
- Education, research, evaluation, prototyping.
- Modifying the source and using your modified version internally.

**Requires a paid commercial license**:
- Installing, deploying, hosting, or configuring this software FOR a paying
  client of yours (e.g. as part of a consulting engagement or paid service
  delivery).
- Selling, reselling, or sublicensing this software, on its own or as part of
  a bundle.
- Offering this software (or a derivative) as a paid hosted / SaaS / managed
  service.
- Embedding this software in a paid product you ship to customers.

If you are unsure whether your use is commercial, contact
**cristian@automwise.com** before deploying. We will respond with either a
written confirmation of noncommercial status (free) or a quote for a commercial
license.

